  • Property Details

    • actionResponder

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<Runnable> actionResponderProperty

      Returns the ObjectProperty containing the Runnable that is executed in a Background Task when this ImageButton is pressed.

      Execution Details

      1. The Runnable is executed in a Background Task by the core Executor for the entire application instance.
      2. The Task execution is non-blocking.
      3. To execute a Runnable on the JavaFX Thread, refer to actionResponderFXProperty().
      4. If the value contained by the ObjectProperty is null, no action response will be executed.
      See Also:
      getActionResponder(), setActionResponder(Runnable)

      public final javafx.beans.property.ReadOnlyBooleanProperty selectedProperty

      Returns the property containing a boolean that reflects if this ImageButton is currently selected or not.

      Changing the Value

      1. To modify the value of the returned property, refer to setSelected(boolean).
      2. Modifications to the returned property can only be modified via the setSelected(boolean) method because the value can only be changed if this ImageButton is toggleable.
      3. Refer to setSelected(boolean) documentation for additional information.
      4. The ImageButtonGroup selection is automatically updated via listener when this value is changed.

    • buttonGroup

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<ImageButtonGroup> buttonGroupProperty

      Returns the ObjectProperty containing the ImageButtonGroup that this ImageButton is in, or null if this ImageButton is not in a ImageButtonGroup.

      Details

      1. All logic related to adding or removing an ImageButton from a ImageButtonGroup is done via a ChangeListener that observes the ObjectProperty returned by this method.
      2. The aforementioned ChangeListener is configured in the ImageButton constructor.
      See Also:
      getButtonGroup(), setButtonGroup(ImageButtonGroup)

    • ImageButton

      public ImageButton​(@NotNull @NotNull net.rgielen.fxweaver.core.FxWeaver weaver, @NotNull @NotNull org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext ctx, @Nullable @Nullable ImagePane imagePane, @NotNull @NotNull javafx.beans.value.ObservableStringValue nameBinding, @Nullable @Nullable Runnable actionResponder, @Nullable @Nullable Runnable actionResponderFX, boolean toggleable, @Nullable @Nullable javafx.geometry.Point2D size)

      Fully-Parameterized Constructor

      Parameter Details

      1. Image Pane: ImagePane

        Refer to getImagePane() for additional information.
        1. If the specified ImagePane is null, a new ImagePane is constructed.
      2. Name Binding: ObservableStringValue
        Refer to nameBinding() for additional information.
        1. If the specified nameBinding is null, a NullPointerException is thrown.
      3. Action Responder: Runnable
        Refer to actionResponderProperty() for additional information.
      4. FX Action Responder: Runnable
        Refer to actionResponderFXProperty() for additional information.
      5. Toggleable: boolean
        Refer to isToggleable() for additional information.
      6. Size
        1. Defines the dimensions of this ImageButton.
        2. More specifically, size defines the dimensions of the Image Pane containing this ImageButton.
        3. If the specified value is null, no size adjustments will be made to the Image Pane, which could result in a distorted image display.
        4. In the future, the size will also be used to load the Image of the correct size using the corresponding size ID.
        5. After being used to set the size of the ImagePane, the size is not stored or otherwise used again.
        6. The getSize() method returns the current dimensions of the Image Pane containing this ImageButton.
      Parameters:
      imagePane - The ImagePane this ImageButton will be displayed on.
      nameBinding - The ObservableStringValue containing the name of this ImageButton.
      actionResponder - The Runnable that is executed in a Background Task when this ImageButton is pressed.
      actionResponderFX - The Runnable that is executed on the JavaFX Thread when this ImageButton is pressed.
      toggleable - True if this ImageButton is toggleable, false if it is not.
      size - A Point2D representing the width and height of this ImageButton.

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public ImageButton initialize()

      Initializes and then returns a self-reference to this ImageButton.

      Initialization Process

      1. Initializes ImagePane.
        1. Constructs an Array of all Observables that will cause the Image for this ImageButton to be Recalculated upon invalidation.
        2. Constructs an ObjectBinding that binds the Image Property of this ImageButton's ImagePane to the value of getImage().
          • Sets the Observales that will trigger a recalculation for the ObjectBinding to the aforementioned Array of Observales.
      2. Configures this ImageButton's ImagePane.
        1. Sets Pick on Bounds to true.
        2. Sets On Mouse Clicked to Consume its Event.
        3. Sets On Mouse Pressed to Consume its Event.
        4. Sets On Mouse Released to execute onMouseReleased(MouseEvent).
      3. Returns a self-reference (this) to this ImageButton. Note that the return value is oftentimes superfluous.
      Returns:
      A self-reference (this) to this ImageButton.

    • setSelected

      public final boolean setSelected​(boolean selected)

      Set the selection state of this ImageButton to the specified value.

      Details

      1. The property returned by selectedProperty() is read-only. Therefore, the selection state of this ImageButton can only be changed via this method.
        1. This is because the selection state can only be modified if the ImageButton is toggleable.
      2. If this method is called but this ImageButton is not toggleable, this method silently returns false.
      3. Refer to selectedProperty() for additional information.
      Parameters:
      selected - True if this ImageButton is being selected, false if it is being deselected.
      Returns:
      True if the selection state of this ImageButton was successfully changed to the specified value, false if it was not.

    • toggle

      public boolean toggle()

      Toggles the selection state of this ImageButton by setting it to the opposite of its current state.

      Passthrough Definition: setSelected(!isSelected())

      Details

      1. If this ImageButton is not toggleable, this method does nothing and silently returns false.
      Returns:
      True if the toggle operation was successful, false if it was not.
      See Also:
      setSelected(boolean)

    • nameBinding

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.binding.StringBinding nameBinding()

      Returns the StringBinding bound to the name of this ImageButton.

      Details

      1. The name is used to load references to the Cached Images.
      2. Each state results in a different variation of the same Image referenced by the ImageButton name.
      3. The getImage() method returns the current Image variation displayed by this ImageButton based on its current state.
      4. The Image variations are essentially each a different styling of the same original image. // TODO - Eventually have styling be done via code automatically.
      5. The StringBinding returned by this method can never return null and will instead return "missingno" if the name is undefined.

      Cache ID

      1. To get the cache ID, refer to the getID() method.
      2. To get the full cache path ID, refer to the getPathID() method.
      Returns:
      The StringBinding bound to the name of this ImageButton.
      See Also:
      getName(), getState(), getImage(), getID(), getPathID()

    • buttonGroupProperty

      @NotNull public @NotNull javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<ImageButtonGroup> buttonGroupProperty()

      Returns the ObjectProperty containing the ImageButtonGroup that this ImageButton is in, or null if this ImageButton is not in a ImageButtonGroup.

      Details

      1. All logic related to adding or removing an ImageButton from a ImageButtonGroup is done via a ChangeListener that observes the ObjectProperty returned by this method.
      2. The aforementioned ChangeListener is configured in the ImageButton constructor.
      See Also:
      getButtonGroup(), setButtonGroup(ImageButtonGroup)
